<HEADLINE>
FT  09 JAN 93 / Finance &amp; The Family: The Week Ahead
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
TOMKINS, the conglomerate which has just bought Ranks Hovis McDougall, the
bakery, milling and baking company, is expected to report on Monday interim
profits of Pounds 47m, up from Pounds 43.7m. Earnings per share are expected
to be up 8 eight per cent. Tomkins is expected to be enjoying the beginnings
of recovery in the US where it has extensive manufacturing operations.
TSB Group reports results for the year to October 31 on Thursday. Brokers
expect a modest recovery to profits of Pounds 80m before tax, against losses
of Pounds 47m in the previous year. The group is thought to have incurred a
big charge, estimated at more than Pounds 400m, to cover possible losses on
bad and doubtful debts. TSB chairman Sir Nicholas Goodison warned last week
that the second half had been unexpectedly bad.
Wednesday sees interim results from Dixons Group. They will depend on how
the electrical retailing group chooses to treat the Pounds 10m property
development profits. Assuming they are not taken at the pre-tax line,
taxable profits of about Pounds 10m are expected, against last time's Pounds
17.5m. Good growth in the UK retail side will lift profits to Pounds 20m
(Pounds 16m), while in the US, losses will also grow to Pounds 14m (Pounds
11m). Its comments on Christmas trading will also be of close interest.
The Rank Organisation, announcing preliminary results on Thursday for the
year ended October, is expected to reveal unchanged trading profits for its
managed businesses. But lower profits are expected at Rank Xerox, its
photocopier joint venture, while profits from its 50 per cent stake in the
Universal Studios theme park in Florida should be significantly higher.
Group pre-tax profits should be slightly lower at Pounds 245m (Pounds
250.5m), with the total dividend unchanged at 31p.
First Leisure is reporting preliminary results on Wednesday for its
financial year ended October. Pre-tax profits are forecast to rise from
Pounds 30.4m to between Pounds 30.6m and Pounds 32m.
