<TEXT>
DE BEERS again led Johannesburg higher with a 5.7 per cent gain as its
shares rose R3.50 to R64. Since Wednesday's announcement of
better-than-expected 1992 diamond sales figures the group has risen nearly
11 per cent. The overall index put on 48 to 3,382, industrials firmed 58 to
4,536 but gold slipped 3 to 790 on a weaker bullion price with Vaal Reefs
losing R2 to R141.
