<HEADLINE>
FT  09 JAN 93 / UK Company News: Platon offer talks terminated
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Platon International, which in October last year announced it was in talks
which might have led to a general offer being made for the company,
yesterday revealed that those discussions had terminated.
Mr Robin Meyer, chairman of the USM-quoted maker of flow, level and pressure
measuring and controlling instruments, said prospects for the second half of
the 1993 year remained encouraging.
Platon's shares closed down 1p at 21p.
</TEXT>
