<HEADLINE>
FT  09 JAN 93 / British troops come under shellfire for first time in Bosnia
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
British troops stationed in Tomislavgrad, Bosnia, came under shellfire for
the first time, presumably from Serbian guns, for about an hour and a half
yesterday afternoon. An officer with the British unit, one of three units of
Royal Engineers responsible for maintaining a critical relief supply road
over the mountains to the central Bosnian town of Vitez, said about 140
shells fell in the immediate vicinity of their base, which lies in a factory
and adjacent school.
No one was injured, but vehicles and equipment were damaged. One officer
said: 'We've expected this for a long time. We don't know if we were the
actual target because there are Croat gun positions right behind the
grounds.'
</TEXT>
