FT  08 JAN 93 / Council tax may bring lower bills
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
THE average council tax bill in England will be lower than the poll tax per
household, according to Local Government Chronicle. Its study of more than
half the councils in England suggests the average council tax bill from
April will be Pounds 505. Allowing for inflation, that is lower than the
average household poll tax of Pounds 500.
