<HEADLINE>
FT  07 JAN 93 / Elf places Pounds 70m N Sea order
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DEBORAH HARGREAVES
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
ELF ENTERPRISE announced the award of a Pounds 70m contract to SLP
Engineering to build an accommodation platform for its Claymore oilfield in
the North Sea yesterday.
The platform will include the up-to-date safety measures in the
accommodation module that are required in the wake of the Cullen report on
the Piper Alpha oil platform tragedy, in which 167 people died in 1988. It
will replace the existing accommodation facilities on the Claymore A
platform and the floating unit moored alongside.
Safety measures on all North Sea facilities must be updated as a result of
recommendations in the Cullen report.
The new 11,000-tonne accommodation platform will be built at SLP
Engineering's two yards at Lowestoft and Teesside. The platform will provide
work for 670 people and is due to be installed in early 1995.
Phillips Petroleum yesterday announced the award of a Pounds 28m contract to
Kvaerner H&amp;G to design and supply facilities for its Judy and Joanne oil and
gas fields in the North Sea.
The company is discussing development plans for the fields with the
Department of Trade and Industry.
</TEXT>
