<BYLINE>
   By ALICE RAWSTHORN
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   PARIS
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
THE Association Francaise des Banques, representing France's banks, is
appealing against yesterday's ruling by a Paris court that it must pay
FFr400,000 (Pounds 46,674) compensation to each of four clients of BCCI,
Alice Rawsthorn reports from Paris. The four lost FFr400,000-FFr2.6bn when
BCCI collapsed two years ago. The AFB had offered to pay them the standard
compensation of FFr105,000.
