FT  07 JAN 93 / EC emigrants 'prefer' France
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   PARIS
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Thirty-five per cent of EC residents are prepared to move to another country
within the Community and most would pick France as their adoptive home,
according to an opinion poll published yesterday, Reuter reports from Paris.
The survey in the daily Le Parisien newspaper said the highest number of
would-be emigrants, 53 per cent, were Dutch, followed by Germans, Britons
and Belgians.
